  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does a selfie stick works with an Android phone?",
  "response": "A selfie stick typically works with an Android phone using either a wired connection or a wireless connection such as Bluetooth. Here\u2019s how each method generally works:\n\n### Wired Connection\n\n1. **Plugging In**: Most wired selfie sticks have a 3.5mm headphone jack at the end of the stick, which you insert into the headphone port of your Android phone (if it has one).\n\n2. **Using the Button**: Once connected, the button on the handle of the selfie stick acts as a shutter button to take photos. When you press this button, the stick sends an electrical signal that the phone registers as a command to capture a photo.\n\n3. **App Compatibility**: In some cases, no special app is needed as the button is recognized by the phone\u2019s default camera app. However, if it doesn't work, you may need to use a different camera app or adjust settings to enable the functionality.\n\n### Wireless (Bluetooth) Connection\n\n1. **Pairing**: Turn on the Bluetooth function on your selfie stick and then on your Android phone. Search for available Bluetooth devices and pair your phone with the selfie stick.\n\n2. **Using the Button**: After successful pairing, the button on the selfie stick works like a Bluetooth remote shutter. Pressing the button sends a signal to the phone to take a photo.\n\n3. **Configuration**: Sometimes, you might need to change the settings in your camera app to recognize the Bluetooth signal as a shutter command. This usually involves selecting the selfie stick option in the camera or settings app.\n\n### General Steps\n\n- **Position the Phone**: Securely attach your Android phone to the clip or mount of the selfie stick, making sure it\u2019s balanced and stable.\n  \n- **Adjust Angle and Length**: Extend the selfie stick to the desired length and angle for your photo.\n\n- **Capture the Photo**: Use the shutter button, whether through a wired connection or Bluetooth, to take your selfie.\n\n### Tips\n\n- **Compatibility**: Check if your Android phone has a headphone jack for wired sticks or Bluetooth capability for wireless ones.\n  \n- **Battery**: If using a Bluetooth model, ensure it is charged or has fresh batteries.\n\n- **Safety**: Make sure the phone is securely clamped to avoid dropping it.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to use your selfie stick efficiently with your Android phone.",
